===Etymology===
From a [[non-alcoholic]] drink called [[w:Claytons|Claytons]] promoted in [[Australia]] and [[New Zealand]] in the 1980s as "the drink you have when you're not having a drink".  It didn't impress [[consumer]]s and the term came to be represent substitution.
